<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-129101" number="67937" version="2027">
			<HEADING>Chapter 57: Petitions for Rulemaking</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17140" name="T28C057"/>Chapter 57: Petitions for Rulemaking</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129102" number="67938" version="2027">
								<HEADING>§ 57-01 Scope.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17184" name="T28C057_57-01"/>§ 57-01 Scope.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129545" number="67939" version="2027">
									<PARA>This chapter governs the procedures by which the public may submit petitions for rulemaking to HPD pursuant to section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1043" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1043</LINK>(g) of <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="Chapter 45" destination-id="0-0-0-0">Chapter 45</LINK> of the New York City Charter, also known as the City Administrative Procedure Act, and the procedures for HPD consideration and disposition of such petitions. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129544" number="67940" version="2027">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 8/6/2021, eff. 9/5/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129514" number="67941" version="2027">
								<HEADING>§ 57-02 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17186" name="T28C057_57-02"/>§ 57-02 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129543" number="67942" version="2027">
									<PARA>As used in this chapter, the following terms have the following meanings. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129542" number="67943" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">HPD.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;HPD&quot; means the Department of Housing Preservation and Development of the City of New York or any successor agency or department thereto. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129541" number="67944" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Person.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Person&quot; means an individual, partnership, corporation or other legal entity, and any individual or entity acting in a fiduciary or representative capacity. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129540" number="67945" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Petition.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Petition&quot; means a request or application for HPD to adopt a Rule. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129539" number="67946" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Petitioner.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Petitioner&quot; means the Person who files a Petition. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129538" number="67947" version="2502">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Rule.</CHARFORMAT> &quot;Rule&quot; has the same meaning as in section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1041" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1041</LINK>(5) of the New York City Charter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129537" number="67948" version="2027">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 8/6/2021, eff. 9/5/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129527" number="67949" version="2027">
								<HEADING>§ 57-03 Procedures for Submitting Petitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17188" name="T28C057_57-03"/>§ 57-03 Procedures for Submitting Petitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129536" number="67950" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any Person may submit a Petition. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129535" number="67951" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Petition must include: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129534" number="67952" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Rule to be considered, with proposed language for adoption; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129533" number="67953" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A statement of the Rule&apos;s purpose and HPD&apos;s authority to promulgate the Rule; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129532" number="67954" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Petitioner&apos;s arguments in support of adopting the Rule; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129531" number="67955" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The period of time the Rule should be in effect; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129530" number="67956" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(5)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The name of the Petitioner or his or her authorized representative and at least one of the following: (A) mailing address, (B) telephone number, or (C) email address; and <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129529" number="67957" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(6)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The signature of the Petitioner or his or her authorized representative. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129528" number="67958" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any change in the information provided pursuant to paragraph five of subdivision b of this section must be reported promptly in writing to HPD by: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129546" number="67959" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>mail or hand delivery to the Office of Legal Affairs of HPD at 100 Gold Street, 5th Floor, New York, New York 10038, ATTN: General Counsel; or <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129547" number="67960" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>e-mail to rules@hpd.nyc.gov. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129526" number="67961" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Petition must be typewritten. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129525" number="67962" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Petition must be: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129548" number="67963" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>mailed or delivered to the Office of Legal Affairs of HPD at 100 Gold Street, 5th Floor, New York, New York 10038, ATTN: General Counsel; or <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129549" number="67964" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>e-mailed to HPD at rules@hpd.nyc.gov. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129524" number="67965" version="2027">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 8/6/2021, eff. 9/5/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129512" number="67966" version="2027">
								<HEADING>§ 57-04 Procedures for Consideration of and Responses to Petitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17190" name="T28C057_57-04"/>§ 57-04 Procedures for Consideration of and Responses to Petitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129523" number="67967" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>When a Petition is submitted to HPD in proper form, HPD will stamp or otherwise register receipt of the Petition with the date it was received and will assign the Petition a number or other unique identifier. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129522" number="67968" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">HPD Response.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129521" number="67969" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>After HPD receives a Petition submitted in proper form, HPD must, within sixty days from the date of the Petition&apos;s receipt, either: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129520" number="67970" version="2027">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(A)<TAB tab-count="1"/>deny the Petition in writing, stating the reasons for denial, or <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129519" number="67971" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(B)<TAB tab-count="1"/>grant the Petition in writing, stating HPD&apos;s intention to initiate rulemaking, by a specified date, concerning the subject of the Petition. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129518" number="67972" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>HPD is not required to grant the entirety of a Petition and is not bound by the language proposed by a Petition. HPD may amend or modify a Petition&apos;s proposed language at HPD&apos;s discretion. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129517" number="67973" version="2027">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 8/6/2021, eff. 9/5/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-129511" number="67974" version="2027">
								<HEADING>§ 57-05 No Appeal.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-17192" name="T28C057_57-05"/>§ 57-05 No Appeal.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129516" number="67975" version="2497">
									<PARA>HPD&apos;s decision to deny or grant a Petition is final and is not subject to judicial review. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-129103" number="67976" version="2027">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 8/6/2021, eff. 9/5/2021) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-064]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>